^Empire Overview
|0B Empires

|0C Every clan, village, and alliance has an empire consisting of buildings,
 an army, developed land, and a gold vault.  Use your empire to attack
 and spy on rivals, steal their land and gold, or destroy their buildings.

 Press |0B(P)|0C from the main menu to manage your clan's empire.  Villagers
 may also donate to the village empire at the Town Hall.  Alliance members
 may manage the alliance empire from the Alliance menu.

 |14Build a Barracks before doing anything else -- you need one to train
 troops or launch an attack.
^END

^Buildings
|0B Buildings

|0C Select |0B(B) Build Structure|0C from the Empire menu to erect buildings.
 Each building consumes developed land, worker energy, and gold.  Worker
 energy resets to 100% each day, so plan your construction carefully.

 Select a building by number to see its stats before buying.  Press |0B(*)|0C
 to demolish a building and recover its land and half its gold cost.

 Available building types:
   Barracks, Walls, Towers, Steel Mill, Stables, Intell. Agencies,
   Security Centers, Gymnasiums, Developer's Halls, Shops (village only)
^END

^Barracks
|0B Barracks

|0C Barracks are required to train troops and to launch attacks.  Each
 Barracks you build increases the maximum number of troops you may keep:

   20 Footmen per Barracks
   10 Axemen per Barracks  (also requires a Steel Mill)
    5 Knights per Barracks  (also requires a Steel Mill and Stables)

 Barracks are well-protected during attacks and are rarely the first
 buildings destroyed.

 Cost: 2500 gold, 15 land, 30% worker energy
^END

^Walls
|0B Walls

|0C Walls are your first line of defense.  During an attack they draw a
 disproportionately large share of enemy fire, shielding your other
 buildings from damage.  Because they absorb so many hits, they are
 also among the first buildings destroyed in battle.

 Walls are cheap and use very little land, so build as many as you can
 afford.  Replacing lost walls quickly is a good defensive habit.

 Cost: 1000 gold, 5 land, 7% worker energy
^END

^Towers
|0B Towers

|0C Towers complement your walls by killing off some attacking troops as
 they advance.  Like walls, they are destroyed relatively easily during
 an attack, but the troop losses they inflict can turn the tide of a
 close battle.

 Build towers after you have a solid wall of Walls in place.

 Cost: 1500 gold, 8 land, 12% worker energy
^END

^Steel Mill
|0B Steel Mill

|0C A Steel Mill is required to produce the weapons and equipment used by
 Axemen and Knights.  Without one, you are limited to training Footmen.

 Only one Steel Mill is needed; building additional mills provides no
 extra benefit.  The Steel Mill uses a large amount of land, so develop
 enough land before attempting to build one.

 Cost: 3000 gold, 20 land, 28% worker energy
^END

^Stables
|0B Stables

|0C Stables house the horses needed to field a cavalry of Knights.  A Steel
 Mill must also be built before Knights can be trained.

 Only one set of Stables is needed.  At 40% worker energy, Stables are
 the most energy-intensive building to construct, so save up your daily
 energy budget before attempting to build them.

 Cost: 5000 gold, 20 land, 40% worker energy
^END

^Intell. Agencies
|0B Intelligence Agencies

|0C Intelligence Agencies train the spies you send against other empires.
 You must have at least one before you can spy.  Each additional agency
 raises the level of your spies, making it easier to penetrate targets
 that have invested in Security Centers.

 Build agencies steadily -- rivals will be building Security Centers to
 counter you, so more agencies helps maintain your edge.

 Cost: 1000 gold, 10 land, 25% worker energy
^END

^Security Centers
|0B Security Centers

|0C Security Centers prevent enemy spies from gathering information about
 your empire.  Each additional center raises the spy level required to
 successfully infiltrate you.

 Security Centers directly counter the enemy's Intelligence Agencies.
 If rivals are actively spying on you, build more Security Centers to
 keep your empire's details hidden.

 Cost: 1000 gold, 10 land, 25% worker energy
^END

^Gymnasiums
|0B Gymnasiums

|0C Gymnasiums keep your troops in peak fighting condition.  Each Gymnasium
 raises your army rating by an additional 2% per day on top of the base
 daily recovery.

 Because army rating decays with every attack, Gymnasiums are a
 long-term investment that pays off over many days of play.  They use
 very little land for their cost, making them efficient to add once
 your core military buildings are in place.

 Cost: 4500 gold, 5 land, 20% worker energy
^END

^Developer's Halls
|0B Developer's Halls

|0C Developer's Halls train workers who convert raw land into usable
 building plots.  Each hall reduces the cost of developing land by
 5 gold per unit, down to a minimum of 20 gold per unit (base: 100).

 Because every building you construct requires developed land, Developer's
 Halls pay for themselves quickly.  Build them as early as possible to
 keep land development affordable throughout the game.

 Cost: 3000 gold, 10 land, 15% worker energy
^END

^Shops
|0B Shops

|0C Shops can only be built by the village.  Each shop earns the village
 approximately 1500 gold per day, providing a steady income stream.

 The village begins with 10 shops at the start of the game.  Building
 additional shops is one of the best ways to grow the village's treasury,
 but they require significant land and energy to construct.

 Cost: 5000 gold, 20 land, 30% worker energy
^END

^Worker Energy
|0B Worker Energy

|0C Worker energy represents your workforce's capacity to construct new
 buildings.  Each building requires a percentage of your total energy
 when built; energy is restored to 100% at the start of each day.

 If you run out of energy you cannot build anything new until tomorrow.
 Plan ahead -- build the most critical structures first each day.
^END

^Army
|0B Army

|0C Select |0B(M) Manage Army|0C to train troops from your pool of Followers.
 A Barracks is required.  Each Barracks supports a fixed number of troops:

   |0B(1)|0C Footmen    15 gold each  (20 per Barracks)
   |0B(2)|0C Axemen     30 gold each  (10 per Barracks; requires Steel Mill)
   |0B(3)|0C Knights    60 gold each  ( 5 per Barracks; requires Steel Mill
                                    and Stables)

 Press |0B(H)|0C inside the Manage Army menu for full troop statistics.

|0B Army Rating

|0C Army rating (shown as a percentage) reflects how well your troops fight.
 A fresh army at 100% deals full damage; rating drops with each attack.
 It recovers 5-10% per day, plus 2% per Gymnasium built.  Send small
 forces to preserve your rating -- a huge army sent repeatedly will
 degrade quickly.
^END

^Attacking
|0B Attacking

|0C Select |0B(A) Attack an Empire|0C to send your army against a target.  A
 Barracks is required.  You will choose the target type (village,
 alliance, or clan), then the specific target, then the troops to send,
 then one of four goals:

   |0B0|0C Oust the Ruler     Remove the current village ruler from power
   |0B1|0C Capture Land       Loot up to 10% of the target's land
   |0B2|0C Capture Gold       Loot up to 15% of the target's gold
   |0B3|0C Destroy Buildings  Damage up to 15% of the target's buildings

 Clans may launch up to 5 attacks per day.  The village army may attack
 up to 2 times per day.  Results (casualties and loot) are returned via
 the next daily reset.

 |14Walls and Towers reduce damage taken -- build them to slow attackers.
 |14Keep your attacking army small to protect your army rating.
^END

^Spy Help
|0C Use a spy to gain information on your enemy's empires.  If your spy is
 "caught", the enemy will be notified of your spying attempt.  You may spy
 up to 10 times a day.

 An Intelligence Agency is required before you can spy.  Each spy attempt
 costs 1000 gold.  The chance of success rises with the number of your
 agencies and falls with the target's Security Centers.  Build more
 Intelligence Agencies to improve your odds; build Security Centers to
 protect yourself from rival spies.
^END

^Donations
|0B Donations

|0C Clans may contribute resources to the village or alliance empire to
 strengthen it for combat.  Donations are made at the Town Hall |0B(E)|0C or
 from the Alliance menu |0B(P)|0C.

 You can donate Followers, Footmen, Axemen, Knights, and Land.

 Village rulers and alliance leaders may also use the Take options to
 withdraw resources from their empire when they need troops or land.

 |04Note: you cannot donate to your own clan's empire from the Empire menu.
^END

^Developing Land
|0B Developing Land

|0C Raw land must be developed before buildings can be erected.  Select
 |0B(L) Develop Land|0C from the Empire menu and enter the number of units you
 wish to convert.

 The base cost is 100 gold per unit, reduced by 5 gold for each
 Developer's Hall you have built, down to a minimum of 20 gold per unit.
 Maximum total developed land is 3000 units.

 |14Build Developer's Halls early -- they pay for themselves quickly by
 cutting the cost of every unit of land you develop afterward.
^END
